   <text>
      <body>
         <pb/>
         <milestone n="80" unit="page"/>
         <lb/>
         <lb/>
         <head>S O N G<lb/>
            <hi>for the</hi>
            <lb/>
            <emph>WANDERING
                                   JEW.<lb/>
               <lb/>
            </emph>
         </head>
         <lg n="1" type="stanza">
            <l n="1">THOUGH the torrents from their fountains</l>
            <l n="2">Roar down many a craggy steep,</l>
            <l n="3">Yet they find among the mountains</l>
            <l n="4">Resting-places calm and deep.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="2" type="stanza">
            <l n="5">Though almost with eagle pinion</l>
            <l n="6">O’er the rocks the Chamois roam,</l>
            <l n="7">Yet he has some small dominion</l>
            <l n="8">Which no doubt he calls his home.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="3">
            <l n="9">If on windy days the Raven</l>
            <l n="10">Gambol like a dancing skiff,</l>
            <l n="11">Not the less he loves his haven</l>
            <l n="12">On the bosom of the cliff.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="4" type="stanza">
            <l n="13">Though the Sea-horse in the ocean</l>
            <l n="14">Own no dear domestic cave;</l>
            <l n="15">Yet he slumbers without motion</l>
            <l n="16">On the calm and silent wave.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="5" type="stanza">
            <l n="17">Day and night my toils redouble!</l>
            <l n="18">Never nearer to the goal,</l>
            <l n="19">Night and day, I feel the trouble,</l>
            <l n="20">Of the Wanderer in my soul.</l>
         </lg>
      </body>
